He and the Dnipro lads organized a lot of useful things for the city. Vanyan loved hardcore music very much and was always present at the concerts of the Dnipro musical band â€œThree Hills Cityâ€. How will it go on? UBFC accompanied the BFC Dynamo club for 11 years and went through many ups and downs. During this time we were able to add new aspects to the atmosphere in the stands and above all to offer young people a home. We hope that these will not be lost in the future either. For us as individuals, the paths will look different and only the future will tell whether and how things will continue in the stadium for the individual or together again at some point. Of course, each of us will always keep the BFC Dynamo and the time in the group with unforgettable people and unforgettable moments in our hearts. Thank you to everyone who has supported us over the years. A first chapter, establishing an ultra scene at BFC Dynamo, is now history. But rest assured it won't be the last. Of course we will leave no stone unturned, we will turn every stone to punish the perpetrators and their entire cowardly scene with all severity. This act will not go unpunished! Death to all enemies of our BFC Dynamo!

Dissolution of the group Ultras BFC With the publication of these lines, we declare the group Ultras BFC dissolved. We are ending all activities and mood support with immediate effect. Why this step? On Friday, January 20th, 2023, after the game against Lichtenberg 47, a person with our material was waylaid in front of his private home. Several masked people jumped out of a car parked in front of the house, hit and kicked suddenly and stole the essential material of our group. A cowardly outnumbered robbery that no doubt required some planning and will one day be avenged with the darkest of wrath and fury. We have also harmed the glorious scene of the BFC Dynamo and would like to apologize for this.

We gather 30 - 35 guys and sit ready in cars just a little bit outside Gothenburg next to the main road at the same time as their game is over. Their bus starts rolling towards Stockholm again and when they are just outside Gothenburg and have about 20-25 minutes left to the location we are waiting, they get a call from us. Something happens there that has no equivalent in history of Swedish football firms. We call the KGB and Hammarby's leaders answer the phone and tell them to just take the exit a couple of kilometers ahead and invite them to a fair fight and where they will get time and space to prepare. They ask to be allowed to return the call in 2 minutes but instead of doing so, all their leaders just stop answering their phones or even turn off their phones.. After giving them the chance to stop the bus at any exit, with no result we choose to drive up next to, in front of and behind the bus to try to stop it and get the KGB to step out but the bus refuses to stop and KGB staying at a safe distance. The KGB is not a firm that wants to fight serious or, for that matter, stands up to be a football firm when it really matters and bangs! The next day, on the day of the Croatia-Ireland match, one of Lech's hooligans with a bandage around his arm approached the Boys in the main square and said: "Good fight. Balkan style ". Later, with Lech, I noticed Cracovia fans who again offered the Boys a "stop", to which ours responded again. Later I heard there was another fight with Lech in a park, but I will not write about it because there are different versions of it, and I was not there. All in all one of the sharper situations I have witnessed

The Poles headed for the Boys on the surrounding road. Not directly across the square, but next to cafes and buildings around the corner where our people were drinking. There was a narrow passage between the cafe where the BBB was and another cafe from which the Poles were heading. The Lechs screwed up. As soon as a friend from Zagreb saw them, he grabbed a chair and shot the first Pole in the head. His example was followed by others of ours. Ashtrays, chairs and bottles began to fly at the Poles. In short, everything that came to our hands. The Poles remained consterned and withdrew, but did not give up. They soon consolidated and they also launched "artillery" towards the Boys. Two Purger lines soon emerged. One towards the narrow passage where the majority of ours stood and the other towards the open space and the square where there were fewer Poles, from where the attacks also came. The narrow passage was easier to defend from the wider area towards the square. Still, at times it was dense. At one point, the Poles squeezed in and approached the Boys, and there was a dangerous exchange of punches. However, ours successfully repulsed all attacks, at one point someone threw a light fixture at the Poles. It all lasted for about 4-5 minutes, after which the police stormed in. Then both ours and the Poles withdrew. Several of us had injuries from pieces of broken glass, and the Poles fared even worse.

Report BBB: My suspicion turned out to be true the very next day. In the afternoon, the BBB team, which I knew well, arrived in the center of Poznan. Guys from ZCB, Sepri, Agram and a few other people from the side tactically occupied one of the cafes in the corner of the square. There were 30-40 good guys there that I mostly knew. I came across a good friend and told him about my last nightâ€™s adventure with Lech fans. He just laughed and told me that since they sat in a cafe, Poles have been visiting them and offering "stops" in nearby parks - 20 by 20, 50 by 50â€¦ anything is possible. He told me that they had turned away all these calls, knowing that in that case the Lechs would have a significant advantage, and they replied very simply to the "deputies": "We are here, in your city and we are not going anywhere. If you want to attack us, we are here. " As the evening approached, our team became more and more drunk, and the Poles became more and more active. I later moved to a coffee shop where I drank last night. Around 11 o'clock in the evening, a Pole with whom I had a party last night approached me and said briefly: "BBB whores!". It was a sign that the fight would almost certainly take place. Soon, 50-60 dangerous-looking characters were created near the cafe. All bald, well-dressed and in tight T-shirts, the so-called "Condoms". I ran to my friend from Zagreb and told him to get ready for the attack because the Lechs are there. I decided to stop right next to the bar where our people were expecting trouble, which soon arrived.

We are now considering as a group what our future will look like and how we will fill it. In our hearts we will always remain Loco and we will never stop fighting against modern football and the great repression from police and club against us. We will always provide Den Bosuil and other stadiums with the biggest pyroshows in Belgium as we have done the last 4 years. We want to thank everyone from the beginning until the end for their support and we promise you that we will come back stronger than ever. ANTWERP LOCOS

After our group experienced an amazing 2 days with a big pyro-show as the highlight, our trip to Frankfurt ended on bad terms. At night, when 3 of our guys returned to the hotel by cab, carrying the Antwerp Locos flag, they were met by a large delegation of Brigade Nassau. Here, after a brawl that could not possibly be won, our group's banner was stolen. When your group's banner is stolen, according to the ultra code you must quit this ultra group. Because of this we have decided, even though it is about a waving flag and not about the main banner, to stop all activities as Antwerp Locos with immediate effect and to disband the group Antwerp Locos. We consider the loss of our waving flag as bad as the loss of a main banner and therefore keep the honor to ourselves. This is a choice we made as a group with respect to the unwritten code (not like they did on the other side of town), but our honor and sense of pride has been hurt too hard.
